Republicans in Georgia are locked in a bitter civil war revolving around the government shutdown and a critical primary race for a shot at unseating Democrat Sen. Jon Ossoff.
Rep. Anna Paulina Luna, R-Fla., discusses the Epstein files and why she believes the disgraced financier may have been connected to foreign intelligence on 'The Will Cain Show.'
Senate Republicans don't object Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer's, D-N.Y., push for Jeffrey Epstein files release vote, follow House's lead after landslide vote to dump the documents.
Sen. Ron Johnson, R-Wisc., discusses a new report adding fresh scrutiny of the shooting targeting President Donald Trump in Butler, Pa. on 'America Reports.'
Uzbek illegal immigrant arrested with Pennsylvania CDL sparks crisis. State Republicans call for investigation into PennDOT licensing practices and oversight.
President Donald Trump said that the only kind of healthcare policy he is willing to back is one that involves money flowing directly to individuals
Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer wants the Senate to vote on the House’s bill to release a trove of Epstein documents.
Reps. Ro Khanna, D-Calif., Thomas Massie, R-Ky., and Marjorie Taylor Greene, R-Ga., demand the Senate pass a bill to release all Jeffrey Epstein files.
Rep. Ro Khanna, D-Calif., Rep. Thomas Massie, R-Ky., and Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene, R-Ga., speak ahead of the upcoming House vote on a bill to compel the release of more Jeffrey Epstein files.
President Donald Trump says he would sign legislation forcing the Justice Department to release all Jeffrey Epstein files as the House prepares to vote.
Political newcomer and former State Department expert David Williams enters race to unseat Democratic Sen. Mark Warner in Virginia's 2026 election.
Trump Organization Executive Vice President Eric Trump argues what Democrats what need to do to have cities 'thrive on their own' on 'Hannity.'

‘Ruthless’ podcast co-hosts Michael Duncan and John Ashbrook discuss the state of leadership in the Democratic party and Michelle Obama remarking that the U.S. is not ready for a woman president on ‘The Story.’
Senator Tammy Duckworth fired staffer Edward York after ICE said he falsely claimed to be attorney for detained illegal immigrant Jose Ismeal Ayuzo Sandoval.
President Donald Trump explains why he wants House Republicans to vote to release the Epstein Files and why he believes the files are a problem for the Democratic Party.
Senate Democrats are calling for an investigation into Trump administration's messaging on government websites during historic shutdown, citing potential federal law violations.
President Donald Trump called Republican Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene of Georgia a "Traitor" to the U.S. in a Truth Social post on Sunday
Healthcare costs now consume nearly one-fifth of America's economy, driving the affordability crisis, but Trump's price transparency order offers a proven solution.
Fox News contributor Hugh Hewitt discusses growing debates about ending the legislative filibuster after the America’s longest government shutdown on ’Sunday Night in America.’
Senate passed spending bill to end government shutdown after complex procedural hurdles and negotiations involving multiple Republican senators.
Democratic strategist James Carville discusses his party’s shift further left, the push to expand the Supreme Court, calls to end the filibuster and more on ‘Saturday in America.’
Sen. John Kennedy, R-La., discusses why New York City and Seattle elected socialist mayors and the push to halt pay for members of Congress during the government shutdown on ‘Saturday in America.’
Democrats accuse Republicans of undermine Medicaid via tax cuts, but Republican lawmakers insist reforms strengthen — not weaken — the federal healthcare program.
Whether the shutdown would actually end remained an open question for much of its duration, but increasing pressure, and a realization that Republicans weren't folding, forced Democrats' hand.
Left-wing group Indivisible targets Senator Chuck Schumer and Democrats who broke ranks to end the federal government shutdown over healthcare disputes.
House and Senate Republicans are at odds over a provision in the federal funding bill that would allow senators to sue over Arctic Frost.

T.W. Arrighi, former NRSC national press secretary, and Meghan Hays, former Biden message planning director, analyze a Wall Street Journal op-ed on Sen. Schumer's government shutdown strategy and discuss potential challenges to Democratic leadership.
Football broadcasting legend Paul Finebaum is taking heat for allegedly being a “Trump-hating" weak Republican amid widespread rumors that he is planning a run for the Senate.
Lengthy federal government shutdown reveals deeper problem of public disengagement as political messaging failures erode belief in democratic institutions and leadership.
Rep. Anna Paulina Luna, R-Fla., comments on the House's vote to end the government shutdown and the Epstein investigation on 'Jesse Watters Primetime.'
